-------- Documentation for tipsv-mpi --------

This is a package for P-SV computation 
for transversely isotropic spherically symmetric media
in the frequency domain.
You need a fortran compiler to run this program.


CONFIGURATION:
	% make

USAGE:
	% tipsv < (parameter filename)


By default, the output spc files will be written in binary format.
To write them in ASCII format, set the parameter 'spcform' to 1
in tipsv.f and mpi-tipsv.f before compiling.


As this is a pre-release version, there should be many defects.
If you have any questions, requests or complaints, please feel
free to contact
  kenji@eps.s.u-tokyo.ac.jp

                                          Kenji Kawai
